70. Create a PHP program to take input, a sequence of numbers from the user and store it in a list or array.
code:
<?php
// Check if form is submitted
if (isset($_POST['numbers'])) {
    // Get input string
    $input = $_POST['numbers'];

    // Split input string by commas, spaces, or semicolons
    $numbers = preg_split("/[,\s;]+/", $input);

    // Convert all elements to numbers (integers or floats)
    $numbers = array_map('floatval', $numbers);

    // Display the array
    echo "Numbers entered:\n";
    print_r($numbers);
}
?>

<!-- HTML form for user input -->
<form method="post">
    Enter numbers separated by comma, space, or semicolon:<br>
    <input type="text" name="numbers" required>
    <input type="submit" value="Submit">
</form>
